  <title>Sims Metal Management CEO Galdino Claro, CFO Fred Knechtel exit </title>
  <content>
Sims Metal has announced the appointment of Alistair Field as chief executive following the immediate departure of Galdino Claro. 
Chief financial officer Fred Knechtel has also left and Amit Patel will take over as acting CFO, the company said on Friday. 
John Clyde will take over Mr Field's role of ANZ Metals managing director.  Mr Field, who has been with the group since October 2015, will be based in New York. 
Chairman Jeff Brunsdon said he was "confident" in Sims Metal's outlook under the new leadership structure.

Sims shares fell 11 per cent at 10.45am AEST to $13.70. 

The scrap metal recycling company is expected to deliver its full-year results on August 25. 
